        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1003465862" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17331759544657416066">You know how the book is going to end from the very beginning. But you still hope. I enjoyed following the relationship between the main characters and how it changed as they got closer. It&apos;s an interesting observation that Remarque makes. You fall for somebody the way they are and they like you for who you are, but then you try to change yourself and the other person because you think that&apos;s how you will like and be liked better. But in reality you just take away the parts you fell in love with</span>
  <span id="freeText17331759544657416066" style="display:none">You know how the book is going to end from the very beginning. But you still hope. I enjoyed following the relationship between the main characters and how it changed as they got closer. It's an interesting observation that Remarque makes. You fall for somebody the way they are and they like you for who you are, but then you try to change yourself and the other person because you think that's how you will like and be liked better. But in reality you just take away the parts you fell in love with.</span>
